The paper deals with the capacity gain achieved through Coordinated Multi-Point (CoMP) transmission in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of simple zero-forcing transmit beams, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper analyzes the capacity of interference channels, which is a topic related to communication engineering (cs.CE).
